{"TopicId":159886,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"NASA SLS/Orion/Payloads","CreatedByName":"_Augustus_","CreatedById":115084,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-28T17:47:51Z","PageNum":61,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-03T18:55:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223343988\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522781697\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157695\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sevenperforce\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, sevenperforce said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCosts about twice as much \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003EdV\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf they spiral out.\u00A0 Why not just do a bunch of periapsis kicks?\u00A0 It would take a long time though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-03T18:58:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223343990\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522781756\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DAL59\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf they spiral out.\u00A0 Why not just do a bunch of periapsis kicks?\u00A0 It would take a long time though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIons give much lower thrust IRL than in KSP. You\u0027d be looking at hundreds or even thousands of periapsis kicks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bill Phil","CreatedById":127797,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-03T20:25:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223343991\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522781898\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157695\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sevenperforce\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, sevenperforce said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIons give much lower thrust IRL than in KSP. You\u0027d be looking at hundreds or even thousands of periapsis kicks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd that\u0027s only if your periapsis is on the day side...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf it can send the station to the Moon then it can put the station and a transfer stage into LEO.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-03T20:29:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.nasaspaceflight.com/2018/04/em-1-update-progress-still-behind-schedule/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.nasaspaceflight.com/2018/04/em-1-update-progress-still-behind-schedule/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStill looking at 2020 (even if they claim late 2019).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-03T21:10:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223343991\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522781898\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157695\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sevenperforce\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, sevenperforce said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIons give much lower thrust IRL than in KSP. You\u0027d be looking at hundreds or even thousands of periapsis kicks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223344052\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522787115\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127797\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bill Phil\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n45 minutes ago, Bill Phil said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd that\u0027s only if your periapsis is on the day side...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf it can send the station to the Moon then it can put the station and a transfer stage into LEO.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1000*90*2=180,000 minutes = 125 days.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe question is, are ion engines infinitely restartable?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-04-03T21:11:10Z\u0022 title=\u002204/03/2018 09:11  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EApril 3, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by DAL59\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-03T22:00:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223344052\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522787115\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127797\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bill Phil\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Bill Phil said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd that\u0027s only if your periapsis is on the day side...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf it can send the station to the Moon then it can put the station and a transfer stage into LEO.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, it IS the transfer stage.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223344076\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522789858\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DAL59\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n39 minutes ago, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1000*90*2=180,000 minutes = 125 days.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe question is, are ion engines infinitely restartable?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo. Deep Space 1\u0027s single ion thruster ran for 10,000 hours but only restarted 34 times.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-04T02:22:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223344116\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522792856\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157695\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sevenperforce\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, sevenperforce said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbut only restarted 34 times.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWas that an actual limit they encountered, or did they just test it that many times?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-04T03:13:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223344299\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522808536\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DAL59\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n53 minutes ago, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWas that an actual limit they encountered, or did they just test it that many times?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat was just the number of restarts in the mission.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"PB666","CreatedById":107380,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-04T13:22:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223344344\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522811597\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157695\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sevenperforce\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, sevenperforce said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat was just the number of restarts in the mission.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey are not restartable an infinite number of times because there is not an infinite amount of fuel, solar panels do not have a infinite life, and eventually the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003EdV\u003C/abbr\u003E imparted on the craft places its source of power (sun) at great distance from those solar panels .\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"wumpus","CreatedById":133850,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-04T13:43:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223343990\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522781756\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DAL59\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 hours ago, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf they spiral out.\u00A0 Why not just do a bunch of periapsis kicks?\u00A0 It would take a long time though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPB666 posted his calculations on this forum.\u00A0 You can cut the fuel needed in half if you are willing to increase the time needed by two orders of magnitude, although the first 10% and 20% add far less time to the voyage (the spreadsheet claims that burning 270 degrees instead of 360 degrees is slightly faster, but thanks to the units this may be a copying error).\u00A0 In practice, I\u0027m reasonably sure it makes more sense to bring the fuel and cut the thrust needed from the ion thrusters.\u00A0 It should be certainly easier to double the Isp (and thus use half the fuel) instead of increasing the thrust by two orders of magnitude (thus making the same trip with half the fuel in the same time by \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003EPe\u003C/abbr\u003E-kicks).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed6090117453\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/168707-how-not-to-burn-for-system-leave/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:211px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"_Augustus_","CreatedById":115084,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-04T18:45:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nApparently pieces of SLS\u0027 SRBs may strike the main engines during launch and cause a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Rapid unplanned disassembly\u0022\u003ERUD\u003C/abbr\u003E. Does NASA know this is a problem? Yes. Will they actually do anything about it? Probably not.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.nasaspaceflight.com/2018/04/em-1-update-progress-still-behind-schedule/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.nasaspaceflight.com/2018/04/em-1-update-progress-still-behind-schedule/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo ipsEmbeddedVideo_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/JDuBLdCaxHo?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInB4 EM-1 \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Rapid unplanned disassembly\u0022\u003ERUD\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-04-04T18:46:41Z\u0022 title=\u002204/04/2018 06:46  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EApril 4, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by _Augustus_\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-04T18:53:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223344930\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522867540\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022115084\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022_Augustus_\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 minutes ago, _Augustus_ said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nApparently pieces of SLS\u0027 SRBs may strike the main engines during launch and cause a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Rapid unplanned disassembly\u0022\u003ERUD\u003C/abbr\u003E. Does NASA know this is a problem? Yes. Will they actually do anything about it? Probably not.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.nasaspaceflight.com/2018/04/em-1-update-progress-still-behind-schedule/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.nasaspaceflight.com/2018/04/em-1-update-progress-still-behind-schedule/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo ipsEmbeddedVideo_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/JDuBLdCaxHo?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInB4 EM-1 \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Rapid unplanned disassembly\u0022\u003ERUD\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAt least there will be a gorram \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Launch Escape System\u0022\u003ELES\u003C/abbr\u003E this time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-04T19:28:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223344941\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522868012\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157695\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sevenperforce\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n32 minutes ago, sevenperforce said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAt least there will be a gorram \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Launch Escape System\u0022\u003ELES\u003C/abbr\u003E this time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe first launch is unmanned though.\u00A0 If it exploded, it would be 8 billion dollars wasted.\u00A0 Oh wait, the SLS is 8 billion wasted anyway...\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223344637\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522848147\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107380\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022PB666\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, PB666 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsolar panels do not have a infinite life\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey would last long enough to get to the moon though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-04T20:09:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n8?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLOL.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m unsure what the numbers are for EM-1, but I remember that by the time EM-2 flies (including that flight), SLS and Orion combined will have cost ~40 B$.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-05T02:14:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223345020\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522872570\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m unsure what the numbers are for EM-1, but I remember that by the time EM-2 flies (including that flight), SLS and Orion combined will have cost ~40 B$.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n40 B would be enough for a 4 person, manned mars mission.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSigh.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bill Phil","CreatedById":127797,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-05T02:54:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223345335\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522894482\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DAL59\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n35 minutes ago, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n40 B would be enough for a 4 person, manned mars mission.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSigh.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo. No it is not. 40 billion wouldn\u0027t even begin a moon base program, let alone a Mars program.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n40 billion is remarkably cheap for Super heavy development, being something like half the Saturn V\u0027s cost to develop. And if BFR can get it cheaper, then that\u0027s great.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMost realistic estimates for Mars missions put the program at about 400\u002B billion, for flags and footprints. Basic stuff.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-05T02:56:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223345363\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522896895\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127797\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bill Phil\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Bill Phil said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMost realistic estimates for Mars missions put the program at about 400\u002B billion, for flags and footprints. Basic stuff.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnless you\u0027re Zubrin, who apparently didn\u0027t even know what ACES was.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"PB666","CreatedById":107380,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-05T03:10:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223345365\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522896974\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 minutes ago, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnless you\u0027re Zubrin, who apparently didn\u0027t even know what ACES was.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWho is Zubrin?\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:wink:\u0022\u003E\u00A0 But seriously why do we mention his name here, h\u0027is is nothing more than a blowhard.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"lugge","CreatedById":143343,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-05T10:15:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223344637\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522848147\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107380\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022PB666\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 hours ago, PB666 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey are not restartable an infinite number of times because there is not an infinite amount of fuel, solar panels do not have a infinite life, and eventually the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003EdV\u003C/abbr\u003E imparted on the craft places its source of power (sun) at great distance from those solar panels .\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCompletely correct answer, and completely useless.\u003Cbr\u003E\nAre you a mathematician? ;-)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-05T19:08:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223345363\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522896895\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127797\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bill Phil\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 hours ago, Bill Phil said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMost realistic estimates for Mars missions put the program at about 400\u002B billion, for flags and footprints. Basic stuff.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou could do a manned mars mission with three sls launches.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.nasa.gov/pdf/376589main_04%20-%20Mars%20Direct%20Power%20Point-7-30-09.pdf\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.nasa.gov/pdf/376589main_04 - Mars Direct Power Point-7-30-09.pdf\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, building several BFRs will not cost 400 billion.\u00A0 We know this because SpaceX does not have 400 billion dollars.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:8px;\u0022\u003EZubrin FTW\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223345363\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522896895\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127797\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bill Phil\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 hours ago, Bill Phil said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n40 billion wouldn\u0027t even begin a moon base program\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNope. 10 billion.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.popularmechanics.com/space/moon-mars/news/a20102/we-could-have-a-moon-base-for-10-billion/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.popularmechanics.com/space/moon-mars/news/a20102/we-could-have-a-moon-base-for-10-billion/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-05T19:46:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223346046\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522955296\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DAL59\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 minutes ago, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou could do a manned mars mission with three sls launches.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.nasa.gov/pdf/376589main_04%20-%20Mars%20Direct%20Power%20Point-7-30-09.pdf\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.nasa.gov/pdf/376589main_04 - Mars Direct Power Point-7-30-09.pdf\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, building several BFRs will not cost 400 billion.\u00A0 We know this because SpaceX does not have 400 billion dollars.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:8px;\u0022\u003EZubrin FTW\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat ancient PDF again. No.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn no particular order:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. Ares != SLS. All the payload masses are wrong. This needs block 2, which is unlikely to exist, IMO, and will take billions more to develop.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. Assuming SLS was magically Ares, they\u0027d need to launch 2 in one launch window. They can\u0027t even launch 2 in one \u003Cem\u003Eyear\u003C/em\u003E, much less days apart.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3. The ECLSS is not ready, the life support we are currently using needs constant repair.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n4. NASA is not doing Mars Direct---nor will they ever---they would do something closer to their DRMs, which are influenced by MD, but involve more redundancy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n5. \u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003EISRU\u003C/abbr\u003E isn\u0027t a thing yet. It needs to be built, then tested before NASA stakes billions and lives on it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNASA is not going to Mars for 10 B$. This project would have to basically assume all the SLS/Orion/DSG costs for a decade. That\u0027s 25 billion just to keep the lights on, right there, before they even launch a Mars vehicle (all of which would have to be built, then tested before the 1st one is ever sent to Mars).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 minutes ago, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNope. 10 billion.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.popularmechanics.com/space/moon-mars/news/a20102/we-could-have-a-moon-base-for-10-billion/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.popularmechanics.com/space/moon-mars/news/a20102/we-could-have-a-moon-base-for-10-billion/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPopular mechanics is certainly an excellent source, lol.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-05T20:28:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223346096\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522957614\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n40 minutes ago, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n. \u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003EISRU\u003C/abbr\u003E isn\u0027t a thing yet. It needs to be built, then tested before NASA stakes billions and lives on it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe sabatier reaction is old.\u00A0 Just send one on the next launch window.\u00A0 They should have put one on the 2020 rover.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223346096\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522957614\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n41 minutes ago, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNASA is not doing Mars Direct---nor will they ever---they would do something closer to their DRMs, which are influenced by MD, but involve more redundancy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThats not the point.\u00A0 I\u0027m saying they\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eshould- \u003C/em\u003Eor more likely some private company.\u00A0 Of course, the BFR doesn\u0027t need the MD architecture.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223346096\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522957614\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n43 minutes ago, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAssuming SLS was magically Ares, they\u0027d need to launch 2 in one launch window. They can\u0027t even launch 2 in one \u003Cem\u003Eyear\u003C/em\u003E, much less days apart.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSend the backup \u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003EISRU\u003C/abbr\u003E a year in advance, stretching the total mission out to 6 years.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223346096\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522957614\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n43 minutes ago, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe ECLSS is not ready, the life support we are currently using needs constant repair.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes the ISS have enough spares currently aboard to last two years at the average failure rate?\u00A0 Now that we have 3-d printers, it could be possible to make a modular, simple LSS designed to be repaired easily with printed parts.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223346096\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522957614\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n46 minutes ago, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. Ares != SLS. All the payload masses are wrong. This needs block 2, which is unlikely to exist, IMO, and will take billions more to develop.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLaunch a second SLS for a TMI stage.\u00A0 Still less than 400 billion.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr use several FH or NG launches.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan you give any example of a mars mission costing\u00A0\u003Cem\u003E400\u00A0\u003C/em\u003E\u003Cem\u003Ebillion\u003C/em\u003E.\u00A0 That\u0027s 200 SLS launches.\u00A0 Or 4,000 FH launches.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-05T20:37:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223346151\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522960092\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DAL59\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe sabatier reaction is old.\u00A0 Just send one on the next launch window.\u00A0 They should have put one on the 2020 rover.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey didn\u0027t.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThats not the point.\u00A0 I\u0027m saying they\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eshould- \u003C/em\u003Eor more likely some private company.\u00A0 Of course, the BFR doesn\u0027t need the MD architecture.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy should they? Why would a private company, where\u0027s the profit? This is the SLS/Orion/DSG thread. It means de facto NASA. Zubrin\u0027s numbers have never been realistic, just as his Moon Direct thing is also unrealistic.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSend the backup \u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003EISRU\u003C/abbr\u003E a year in advance, stretching the total mission out to 6 years.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou have to send anything 2 years in advance (because orbital mechanics).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHis minimalistic mission architecture ain\u0027t happening.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bill Phil","CreatedById":127797,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-05T21:25:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223346046\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522955296\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DAL59\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou could do a manned mars mission with three sls launches.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.nasa.gov/pdf/376589main_04%20-%20Mars%20Direct%20Power%20Point-7-30-09.pdf\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.nasa.gov/pdf/376589main_04 - Mars Direct Power Point-7-30-09.pdf\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, building several BFRs will not cost 400 billion.\u00A0 We know this because SpaceX does not have 400 billion dollars.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:8px;\u0022\u003EZubrin FTW\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNope. 10 billion.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.popularmechanics.com/space/moon-mars/news/a20102/we-could-have-a-moon-base-for-10-billion/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.popularmechanics.com/space/moon-mars/news/a20102/we-could-have-a-moon-base-for-10-billion/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s an interesting thing about space exploration: payloads cost more than launches.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCuriosity cost a few billion, for less than a tonne of payload on the surface of Mars. We can expect manned hardware to be even more complex, so the cost would be higher. Using SLS will increase that cost even more. BFR might shave off a few billion. Maybe tens of billions, if we\u0027re lucky. But it will still be hundreds of billions of dollars for the program, consisting of maybe 6 landings, a la Apollo. Maybe even some around the same time? Would be cool, but unlikely.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve talked to some NASA engineers working at MSFC. It\u0027ll take something like 7 SLS launches. At 3 billion per launch, plus 3 billion per payload, that\u0027s 42 billion. That\u0027s being generous (SLS will be more expensive, payloads too), but we only just got started. Adding in 15 years of paying off salaries and benefits for 10k people (about 250k per person, from what I can find), that\u0027s about 80 billion total. For the first mission, and an extra 42 per mission after that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd that is guaranteed to be a gross\u00A0underestimate. NASA has tens of thousands of contractor employees that work on NASA programs, and we\u0027ve ignored the yearly SLS cost, the SLS development cost, and so on.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-04-05T21:25:41Z\u0022 title=\u002204/05/2018 09:25  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EApril 5, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Bill Phil\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"wumpus","CreatedById":133850,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-05T22:57:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223346222\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022159886\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221522963502\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127797\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bill Phil\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Bill Phil said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s an interesting thing about space exploration: payloads cost more than launches.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJPL must also charge some serious bucks to drive Curiosity and the other rovers all over Mars (even doing experiments and maintaining with stuck rovers isn\u0027t going to be much cheaper).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the 1970s NASA would build at least two copies of various probes (like Voyager 1 \u0026amp; 2).\u00A0 While building the first article was required a full-blown R\u0026amp;D budget, the cost of the second was a tiny percentage of the first.\u00A0 Obviously you needed two launchers (at full cost) and ground control couldn\u0027t have been much cheaper (although I\u0027m certain it made finding backups easier).\u00A0 Eventually they decided that two launches was one too many (probably during the \u0022everything launches from the Shuttle\u0022 era) and they stopped doing that (but somewhat revived the concept with the Mars rovers).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReducing the cost of the payload is generally not seen as sexy as launching rockets, but Bigelow appears to be bringing at least some private megabucks in \u0022dry mass\u0022 spacecraft.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}